Let your forecast be slightly underestimated, but at least you won't make such a big mistake, because this is a square in which the biggest mistakes happen most often. And, in fact, the probability of the forecast is 10-20%. Depending on the qualifications and experience of the managers, you choose what you want to take, 10 or 20%, and, in fact, multiply this number.

