As a result, you get an accurate sales forecast for the Ansoff matrix. And this number will already be your plan. Of course, if it turns out to be very small, and this does not correspond to the request or the task of the owner, then go back a few steps back and start analyzing the key clients again.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:47.000
Start thinking about what and how you can increase or decrease somewhere, don't take something into account, think about where else you can change the forecast. If we get an inadequate number, we go back to step number 2 and start the process again.

01:12:47.000 --> 01:13:08.000
Well, the next step, when we already have the volume, is, if you remember, according to the ABC analysis, these are those 20% of clients who make 80% of the sales volume. So, how can we see the rest of the 20% of the turnover? It's very easy to make a proportion.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:32.000
There are many small clients left. We will not waste time calculating each of them. This is not reasonable. Someone will come, someone will stay, someone will change their conditions. It can be different. Therefore, we will just make a proportion. The proportion is such that we calculated 80% of the turnover, we take another 20% and get the total sales figure.

01:13:32.000 --> 01:13:53.000
The next step is detailing. The total figure does not tell us anything, except for the goals that the company sets for itself. Detailing allows us to plan the work of each manager. What do we do here? Detailing is done as follows. We take the sales channel, it can be an opt, a retail, corporate clients.

01:13:53.000 --> 01:14:14.000
Next, we take the region separately, because, look, each region can have its own dynamics. Marketologists take this into account and give the dynamics of development in directions, taking into account the regions. Therefore, it is necessary to divide regions.

01:14:24.000 --> 01:14:42.000
The regional division will not give an optimal result. You choose how to classify this forecast. The client is chosen, the first, second, third, and so on. And for each client, a sales plan is made in this section.

01:14:42.000 --> 01:15:03.000
Now this annual plan is detailed monthly, taking into account the seasonality coefficients. Seasonality coefficients, for example, are given at the bottom of the slide on the third table. And you can see, it is done very easily, according to statistics, the total sales volume is taken per year.

01:15:04.000 --> 01:15:23.000
Then the average is calculated, and the coefficients are set relative to this average. For example, in January, 0.7 is sold from the average, and so on. And such seasonality coefficients, I want to say, should be individual for each group of goods.

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:41.000
If you have several groups of goods, if there is a single product, then there are no questions, and one table is suitable for all questions. And, taking into account the seasonality coefficients, taking into account the seasonal jumps or falls, we detail the total figure, which we got per month, per group of goods.

01:15:41.000 --> 01:15:59.000
As a result, you get a clear plan for each client, for each month, for each assortment, for each sales channel. And you know why this figure turned out. Where did it come from? And it is very easy to manage these sales.

01:15:59.000 --> 01:16:04.000
What should be done next?

01:16:29.000 --> 01:16:45.000
It is very important to make a strategic forecast for 3 to 3.5 years. I want to say that if you introduce new products, and now most companies do it, a strategic forecast is extremely important, because most often in a year the product is not paid for.

01:16:45.000 --> 01:17:04.000
And your owner simply will not spend money without understanding what the result will be. That is why a strategic forecast for at least 3 years is the most relevant for today. Even our government has already signed a budget for 3 years. This is a sign.

01:17:04.000 --> 01:17:24.000
Therefore, I recommend you to make such forecasts. Of course, no one says that they will come true 100%, but it is still a plan, you know, according to which you go and you can track deviations and take some actions. If you have not planned anything, then you will not take any actions, or they will be chaotic.

01:17:24.000 --> 01:17:39.000
Well, I think that a year plan is made by 100% of companies. Therefore, the plan that we discussed in the previous slide is a year plan, how it can be detailed. Therefore, such a system is almost everywhere in companies.

01:17:39.000 --> 01:18:03.000
Next point. A quarterly, monthly or semi-annual planning. Here I want to give one recommendation. In my experience, it turned out that in addition to the annual planning, the semi-annual also gives very good results, and the quarterly one. It allows you to understand how much the forecast is broken down and whether it needs to be corrected.

01:18:03.000 --> 01:18:22.000
And during the annual planning, we introduced such a system. The total figure per year, provided that there are no strong force majeure factors, should not change. But within this year, our company, our client, can change some of its forecasts.

01:18:22.000 --> 01:18:50.000
For example, it turned out that they did not calculate, bought more than necessary, and then they cannot sell. Why should the company bear additional warehouse costs? They have the right to correct their sales plan in three months, in a quarter, and say, guys, we wanted to take 100,000 products for the next quarter, but we will probably take only 80,000, because we have such circumstances.

01:18:50.000 --> 01:19:19.000
But in the next year we will correct our figures. When it is done in three months, it can be taken into account, because we have not yet produced or bought the product, at least we will not bear these warehouse costs. Imagine if they say this a week before the purchase. Then we can hardly afford it, because then we will lose our profitability.

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:44.000
And when you set such rules, the client understands that he can think in advance, and right before the purchase he is no longer able to change his plans. This also makes the client think, analyze the situation and prevent such things that actually give additional costs and help to plan your business and his too.

01:19:45.000 --> 01:20:10.000
The next point is to include suppliers and customers in the forecasting system. We have already talked about customers, but suppliers are also an important point. Why? Because if you buy a certain amount of components or finished products, the larger the batch, the lower the cost of production.

01:20:11.000 --> 01:20:31.000
And here we must calculate such an optimal batch in order to save some of our resources, including financial, logistical and any. And on the other hand, not to allow the situation called out of stock. This is a product when there are no necessary positions in the warehouse.

01:20:31.000 --> 01:21:00.000
This leads to a decrease in profit and turnover. Therefore, it is advisable to include suppliers in the planning system, especially large ones, depending on the situation. And so you can achieve better delivery conditions.

01:21:01.000 --> 01:21:23.000
The next point is to monitor and control your figures. This is a constant control. In different companies, someone analyzes sales once a month, someone does it once every 10 days.

01:21:23.000 --> 01:21:38.000
The more quickly your product is wrapped, the more often you need to analyze sales. Because when you do it according to the results of a planned period, for example, a month or a quarter, you can't change anything, you can only change future events.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:22:01.000
And when you carry out operational control once every 10 days or once every 2 weeks, you have some tools that you can use to correct the sales plan, to undertake something, to launch some additional incentive program, to give some advertising, to provide some conditions to the supplier, and so on.

01:22:01.000 --> 01:22:15.000
You can play with prices, there are many options. But the main thing is that you can do it in the process without getting a negative result. This is the main meaning of the control system in all this.

01:22:15.000 --> 01:22:34.000
I would like to say separately what such a control system or forecasting system gives us. The first is that the managers themselves participate in the composition of the plan. No one imposes it on them from above, they clearly analyze and understand the main thing, how they can implement this plan.

01:22:34.000 --> 01:23:01.000
That is, the motivation of your managers is greatly increased. The second point is that you increase their qualification. Not every manager, you must agree, participates in the planning system and can do it competently. And a manager who knows how to do it, knows how to plan his relations with clients. And this is very important. Because knowing how to plan, we can manage. Without planning, we do not manage anything, we obey the circumstances that exist.

01:23:01.000 --> 01:23:16.000
I would like to say that not only material motivation, but also moral, plays a role here. Because there is simply a belief that plans can be implemented, that these are some unreachable quantities. And this is very important.

01:23:16.000 --> 01:23:35.000
And not only that, but the knowledge of the client is also increasing, relations with the client are improving. Because in this case, the client is not just imposed, but consulted, discussed. And this makes your relationship with the client partner.

01:23:35.000 --> 01:24:00.000
I would like to say a few words about the procedure for adjusting the plan and what needs to be prescribed. Each company has its own procedure, so the most important thing is to answer the questions that exist. First, who implements the adjustment of the plan? Who has the right to do this? Second, when and how often? Third, based on what information? And who approves the changes in this plan?

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:12.000
These points are very important. And here a short instruction is prescribed, literally, who is responsible for what process, and so that everyone clearly understands and knows this. And then the implementation takes place.

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:32.000
Step 10 is approval. I did not consider it separately. Each company approves in different ways. Somewhere the board of directors approves the sales plan, somewhere the general director just signs it. Sometimes it is given to the owner to study, to calculate the budget, and then to the approval.

01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:50.000
Each procedure has its own procedure. Therefore, the most important thing is that the plan must be signed, approved and accepted for use. We have a detailed plan for clients, so each manager has a clear work plan, what he should do, how and on what assortment.

01:24:50.000 --> 01:25:11.000
But it often happens that the plan that is designed, made, for some reason does not suit the management, because the managers are ambitious and they always want to somehow increase the figure that is obtained. Here on the slide there is a method of finding opportunities for sales growth.

01:25:12.000 --> 01:25:28.000
This is to look again, but if suddenly the plan does not suit, the figure does not suit, let's see what can we do to improve our sales. This method was developed by Jean-Jacques Lambin and offers it in his book Management focused on the market.

01:25:28.000 --> 01:25:40.000
The method is very simple, logical steps that make everyone who participates in the sales forecast in the company think. How else can you increase your sales? Let's look at the very beginning.

01:25:40.000 --> 01:26:01.000
The first step is to put things in order in the company, or to protect the position. What should be done here? Of course, you need to look at whether the sales department is adequate for the tasks that are set. Maybe there are not enough managers, maybe they do not have the qualifications that are necessary for the sale of some complex product.

01:26:02.000 --> 01:26:30.000
Maybe it is necessary to train people so that they can communicate competently and well. Therefore, here, of course, you need to first look at whether everything is in order in the company, whether the business processes are working, whether the tasks are clearly set, whether people have been given a tool for implementation, a program of motivation, advertising opportunities, loyalty programs for clients, and so on.

01:26:30.000 --> 01:26:39.000
There are a lot of tools, you can manage the price, so here the most important thing is to understand whether we have done everything so that the company works stably and well.

01:26:40.000 --> 01:26:54.000
If everything is in order, or you have already put things in order, and, of course, the sales volume has increased, in my practice, only due to this point, there was an increase of 42% of the turnover.

01:26:54.000 --> 01:27:10.000
When they simply put things in order, gave people the right instructions, taught them to work, gave tasks that were clear and clear, 42% increase in turnover in an almost not very actively growing market.

01:27:10.000 --> 01:27:19.000
Well, if we have protected our position, what do we do next? We look at whether we can compete with competitors, because they choose us as part of the clients.

01:27:19.000 --> 01:27:35.000
But there is a certain subtlety, if your company is large, serious, you can afford it. If you work in a medium-sized business or a small one, then do not risk touching your competitors, because they can simply crush you in return.

01:27:35.000 --> 01:27:54.000
Most often, there is a very large outflow of funds, financial resources and personnel resources for competing. Therefore, the most important thing is to comply with such conditions, compliance with parity on the market.

01:27:54.000 --> 01:28:04.000
My favorite saying about competitors is like that of the dead, either good or nothing, it is better not to touch. If you have the opportunity to fight, fight.

01:28:04.000 --> 01:28:18.000
The next point to work on is to increase or stimulate the use, make people use your product more often, buy it more often, consume it more often, anything.

01:28:18.000 --> 01:28:40.000
There are many examples of this on the market, when a fashion is created for a particular product, a particular product, a particular product, when we are constantly forced to change mobile phones, which do not stop ringing, they just add functions that have nothing to do with the phone itself, but nevertheless everything is being updated.

01:28:40.000 --> 01:29:01.000
And we are forced to chase this fashion, because we live in a constantly changing world, this is normal. Think about it, can you apply some tool to your product that would make you buy it more often, consume it more often, use it more often, and this will also give a certain increase.

01:29:01.000 --> 01:29:13.000
The next point I would like to talk about is, of course, the expansion of the sales geography. For example, you have a certain customer base, certain regions where you sell, or maybe you want to go to another country.

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:27.000
We have, for example, many neighboring countries, Belarus, Kazakhstan, Ukraine, which are very similar to us, and we can easily work with our products there. Why not? Or maybe you have more ambitious plans.

01:29:27.000 --> 01:29:54.000
So think about it, due to the fact that you will go to another geographical market, you will naturally increase sales. And the last point, the addition of a range of products. Maybe you should introduce some new product that is super popular on the market, but is not yet in your range. If you introduce it, you will also increase your sales. These are the main opportunities that will allow you to increase your sales.

01:29:54.000 --> 01:30:09.000
Well, using the technique I just told you about, you can model your sales volume, that is, understand what can be another increase. The diagram clearly shows what the company is increasing in sales.

01:30:09.000 --> 01:30:35.000
Due to the increase in marketing activity, due to the release to new regions, due to the addition of a new product, and due to the growth of the market itself. Here is a clear detailed plan, or the detailing of this plan allows both owners and managers to understand what we are doing with you, the figure on which we are tasked.

01:30:35.000 --> 01:31:04.000
In conclusion, I would like to say a few words about what will change in the planning system if you apply this proposed methodology. The first is, of course, the introduction of individual planning for key clients. As I said, this allows them to manage, not just go with the flow, but to manage the situation. This is the most important thing, because key clients, as we remember, give 80% turnover. This is the most important thing for the stability of the company.

01:31:05.000 --> 01:31:27.000
The next point is the accounting of the growth of key client businesses. Maybe we didn't take this into account, didn't ask. Well, they may grow, or maybe they don't grow. Or in fact, we have already determined that either additional deliveries are needed, or something else, or an additional assortment, which also caused chaos in the company's work.

01:31:27.000 --> 01:31:47.000
Therefore, when we know the plans for the growth of key clients, for the growth of their business, it is no longer chaos for us, but a planned, clear work. The next important point is the alignment of planning from above and below. Below are the sales managers, above are the managers and the marketing department. Why from above? Because it gives a general market situation.

01:31:47.000 --> 01:32:07.000
This is the only reason why when these plans meet, the truth is hidden. Because sales managers often lower the plans, and managers often increase them, because they do not know the features of working with a client.

01:32:07.000 --> 01:32:27.000
The next point is the attraction of managers to the development of sales plans. Often this is not done in companies, but if you attract them, you get many advantages. As I said, their training, management of clients, understanding of the process, motivation, all this plays a very good role in the result.

01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:54.000
And, in fact, an effective motivation system that allows you not only to fulfill the plan you have set, but also to be progressive, that is, when you do more than 100%, for example, the manager is motivated in a progressive attitude, naturally, this gives the manager the incentive not only to stay within these limits, but to go higher and increases your profitability of the business, your turnover and your stability.

01:32:54.000 --> 01:33:16.000
The question arises, maybe you don't need to change anything, maybe you should leave everything as it is, live, work, even develop. But the market situation often changes, and the forecasting system cannot be introduced in one year and get a 100% guarantee of what you have.

01:33:16.000 --> 01:33:31.000
The forecasting system is a system because the result is clear over time. The earlier you do it, the faster you will bypass your competitors.

01:33:31.000 --> 01:33:50.000
Therefore, the forecasting system changes to take into account some factors. For example, planning from below will never give the desired result for the managers. Planning from above does not take into account the specificities of the clients.

01:33:50.000 --> 01:34:12.000
And another important point is that planned work will help you to optimally determine the necessary resources for achieving this plan. As we said at the very beginning, these are people, money, technical capabilities, warehouse areas, etc.

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:39.000
That is, you will have a clear and understandable work of planning. Therefore, we get the result we were striving for. The setting of clear tasks, the clear work of the logistics system, the supply system, the clear work of the commercial service, the clear work of the marketing department, which provides support for sales in terms of incentives, advertising, optimization of all these costs,

01:34:39.000 --> 01:35:03.000
and the achievement of the result we planned at the beginning. As a conclusion, I would like to make some objections to the managers of the company or business participants. Why don't you want to make a system? Why is it probably not necessary yet? And try to refute them.

01:35:03.000 --> 01:35:17.000
The first objection is that we do not need sales forecasting. We have a clear market, clients have been working with us for a long time, the main ones, new ones appear rarely, and we live well without a forecasting system.

01:35:17.000 --> 01:35:43.000
What I want to say here is that the market in Russia is not very competitive yet, but day by day the competition is growing, new companies appear, new directions in business that will soon bite off pieces from the company. Therefore, if we want the stability of the business, if we want a clear tomorrow, then planning is necessary.

01:35:43.000 --> 01:36:00.000
What will planning give us? First, of course, it will provide access to client information. Second, it will reduce costs for logistics, for warehouse costs. Further, it will correctly distribute resources, absolutely.

01:36:00.000 --> 01:36:23.000
And most importantly, it will allow us to predict both positive and negative moments in advance. Because positive moments are good, we all perceive them well, we are happy about them. And negative moments, if we at least predict that they can happen, we will have the opportunity to take some actions to reduce their influence on the business of the company.

01:36:24.000 --> 01:36:47.000
The next objection I would like to make is that many companies, especially from the market of services, say that they cannot predict our situation, we do not know what client will come tomorrow, how we will work with him, what he will do for us. But this is all because the market is not stable enough. And the more unstable the market, the less opportunities for forecasting.

01:36:47.000 --> 01:37:05.000
But the market is stabilizing. And we say that year by year it becomes more clear and transparent. The sooner we start forecasting, the sooner we will see which factors affect our activity the most. And that is why we will have the opportunity to clearly understand the situation.

01:37:05.000 --> 01:37:22.000
I want to give you an example. The company I worked with was a printing company that provided printing services. And it printed booklets, self-adhesive labels, and so on. All services provided by any printing company.

01:37:22.000 --> 01:37:42.000
And when we talked to the owner, he had the main objection that in our case we cannot predict, we do not know how many products will be ordered tomorrow, how many of this, what catalogs will be printed. But by introducing such a planning system, this company received the result even in the first year.

01:37:42.000 --> 01:38:00.000
The owner began to clearly understand. Also, clients were divided according to the ABC analysis. According to the key, the planning was very serious and detailed. And according to the rest of the clients, of course, everything was calculated in proportion.

01:38:00.000 --> 01:38:27.000
But the management of key clients allowed him to clearly plan his business. And thanks to this, he was able to calculate his expenses, his resources, and bring additional resources for another, for a new direction, on which he is now one of the Russian leaders. Therefore, plan and predict, regardless of what area you work in.

01:38:27.000 --> 01:38:52.000
The next point. Forecasts can only be rainbow. We predict and we always grow. In fact, it does not always happen. And you have to take this seriously. If the forecast does not increase our sales, then it is a bad forecast. The managers say, nothing like that. You need to understand why it is so. And understand if we can influence these factors to increase the forecast.

01:38:52.000 --> 01:39:10.000
We got a picture of the market and have not yet influenced it. And we can influence suppliers, clients, and buyers. We have the cards in our hands. If the forecast is negative, it does not mean that it is bad. It means that you need to think about how to make it different.

01:39:10.000 --> 01:39:30.000
And one more important point. Or one very important objection. When they say that the forecasting system should work from the first year and should give accuracy of about 100%. And if it does not, then it does not work.

01:39:30.000 --> 01:39:54.000
In fact, many companies are burned out. Having made such a system once and not getting the accuracy they wanted, they quit. In fact, the situation is very serious. And I want to say in practice that forecasting gives accuracy of 90-95% only for about the third year of planning.

01:39:54.000 --> 01:40:12.000
Why? Because when we plan for the first time, we can not count and do not even know what factors can influence us. And most often the forecast of the first year is more optimistic, more rainbow than the situation on the market.

01:40:12.000 --> 01:40:32.000
The second year is very careful, because the first time they got burned out and if they began to plan further, continued, found courage in themselves, then the indicators are usually lowered. But in these two years, the company clearly understands how and what needs to be taken into account, how to plan.

01:40:42.000 --> 01:40:55.000
And this is the stability of the business. Therefore, if you have already taken to make a system, do not throw it halfway, but try to continue and get the result. The result will be accurate.

01:41:25.000 --> 01:41:47.000
And now, when you are armed with this technique, you can start using it in your company or recommend it for use. And I want to say that the process itself is not a guarantee that something will happen.

01:41:47.000 --> 01:41:59.000
Of course, the company must make clear efforts to achieve the goals set in advance. Good luck in your business and good luck. All the best, goodbye.
